# Email Configuration for Nodemailer

# Gmail Configuration (Recommended)
EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password
CONTACT_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# Alternative SMTP Configuration (uncomment if not using Gmail)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.your-provider.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# EMAIL_USER=your-email@domain.com
# EMAIL_PASS=your-password
# CONTACT_EMAIL=contact@yourdomain.com

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local (for local development) or set these in Vercel dashboard
# 2. For Gmail:
#    - Enable 2FA on your Google account
#    - Generate an "App Password" (not your regular password)
#    - Use the app password in EMAIL_PASS
# 3. For other email providers, use their SMTP settings
# 4. CONTACT_EMAIL is where you'll receive the contact form submissions
